Custom annotation supported based on Gson. It validates the required fields marked with the annotation and does the strict parsing.
Inspired by http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14242236/let-gson-throw-exceptions-on-wrong-types/14245807#14245807

Usage:

1. Add the specified annotation "JsonRequired" for required field :

'''
public class TestAnnotationBean {
    @JsonRequired
    public String foo;

    public String bar;
}
'''

2. Register the deserializer :
 '''
 gson = new GsonBuilder()
         .registerTypeHierarchyAdapter(TestAnnotationBean.class,
                 new AnnotatedDeserializer<TestAnnotationBean>())
         .create();
 '''

3. Parse String to actual object.